videos.headline: Wilton Speight starting under center for Michigan
videos.description: Wilton Speight starting under center for Michigan

videos.headline: Ohio State can't take the lead with missed field goal
videos.description: Ohio State's impressive first drive ends without points when Tyler Durbin pulls his field goal attempt wide left to keep the game scoreless.

videos.headline: Michigan on the board first with 28-yard field goal
videos.description: Michigan's drive stalls deep in Ohio State territory, leaving Kenny Allen to drill a 28-yard field goal to give the Wolverines the first points of the game.

videos.headline: Ohio State first in the end zone with pick-six
videos.description: Ohio State gets pressure on Wilton Speight forcing his pass short to get intercepted by Malik Hooker and returned 16 yards for the touchdown to give the Buckeyes their first lead of the day at 7-3.

videos.headline: Michigan takes lead as tempers flare
videos.description: Michigan FB Khalid Hill powers up the middle for a 1-yard touchdown giving the Wolverines a 10-7 lead over Ohio State. Tensions rise after the play as both Ohio State and Michigan get involved in a scuffle.

videos.headline: Peppers makes the pick off the deflection
videos.description: The Michigan pressure gets to J.T. Barrett forcing him to throw the ball high that takes a deflection off the Ohio State receiver and right to Jabrill Peppers for the first Buckeyes turnover of the game.

videos.headline: Michigan drive ends with fumble at the goal line
videos.description: Off a Jabrill Peppers interception, Michigan fails to capitalize as Wilton Speight fumbles the snap at the goal line that is recovered by Ohio State to deny the Wolverines.

videos.headline: Fake punt backfires for the Buckeyes
videos.description: Facing 4th-and-6 from deep in their own territory, Ohio State punter Cameron Johnston takes off but comes up short giving Michigan the ball.

videos.headline: Hill back in the end zone for Michigan
videos.description: After scoring a rushing touchdown earlier, Khalid Hill sneaks out to the flat and makes the catch to go 8-yards for the touchdown increasing Michigan's lead to 17-7.

videos.headline: Ohio State in business after Speight picked again
videos.description: With Michigan having the momentum, Wilton Speight gets picked off by Jerome Baker putting Ohio State into scoring position.

videos.headline: Harbaugh gets penalty for unsportsmanlike conduct
videos.description: Being frustrated with an offsides call against his team, Jim Harbaugh picks up another penalty for unsportsmanlike conduct that moves Ohio State deeper into Michigan territory.

videos.headline: Weber goes over the top for the Ohio State TD
videos.description: Ohio State capitalizes on the Michigan interception when Mike Weber dives over the top to punch it in from a yard out to bring the Buckeyes closer at 17-14.

videos.headline: J.T. Barrett run for 41-yards for a 1ST down
videos.description: J.T. Barrett run for 41-yards to the Mich 22 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Ohio State converts on 4th and 1
videos.description: Mike Weber run for 4 yds to the Mich 9 for a 1ST down

videos.headline: Ohio State misses 20-yard chip shot to tie game
videos.description: Having already missed a 37-yard field goal, Tyler Durbin misses again, this time from 20 yards out to spoil the Ohio State drive to keep Michigan in the lead at 17-14.

videos.headline: Redemption for Durbin sends Buckeyes to OT
videos.description: With two short misses already on the day, Tyler Durbin drills a 23-yard field goal to send Ohio State and Michigan to overtime.

videos.headline: Barrett keeper puts Ohio State up in OT
videos.description: In the first possession of overtime, J.T. Barrett takes the keeper up the middle for the touchdown giving Ohio State a 24-17 lead.

videos.headline: Fourth down TD in OT keeps Michigan alive
videos.description: Facing 4th-and-goal from the five yard line, Wilton Speight finds Amara Darboh in the back of the end zone to send Michigan and Ohio State to double overtime.

videos.headline: Michigan hits 37-yard FG to open 2nd OT
videos.description: Kenny Allen 37-yard FG GOOD

videos.headline: Ohio State extends game on fourth-down gain
videos.description: J.T. Barrett runs for a 1-yard gain to the Michigan 15 for a first down.

videos.headline: Samuel's TD wins the game for Ohio State in 2OT
videos.description: Curtis Samuel takes the sweep and finds the end zone from 15 yards out to score the winning touchdown for Ohio State in double overtime.

videos.headline: Kanell tells Harbaugh to 'get over' officiating
videos.description: Danny Kanell doesn't want to hear Jim Harbaugh complaining about the officiating after Michigan lost to Ohio State.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Kanell tells Harbaugh to 'get over' officiating) 2016/11/26

videos.headline: Samuel proves to be the OT hero for Ohio State
videos.description: Ohio State RB Curtis Samuel comes up clutch in overtime, including scoring the game-winning touchdown for the Buckeyes to give them the victory over Michigan.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Samuel proves to be the OT hero for Ohio State) 2016/11/26 ESHEET

videos.headline: Meyer calls Michigan-Ohio State an 'instant classic'
videos.description: Urban Meyer has high praise for the drama that ensued between Michigan and Ohio State.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Meyer calls Michigan-Ohio State an 'instant classic') 2016/11/26 ESHEET

videos.headline: Meyer's wife interrupts his news conference with phone call
videos.description: Urban Meyer takes a phone call from his wife during his news conference and says he's instructed to bring home a gallon of milk.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Meyer's wife interrupts his news conference with phone call) 2016/11/26 ESHEET

videos.headline: Peppers shoves Ohio State fan
videos.description: After Ohio State defeated Michigan 30-27, Jabrill Peppers encounters an Ohio State fan rushing onto the field and pushes him out of his way.

videos.headline: Ohio State safe in CFP Rankings - for now
videos.description: After its win Saturday over No. 3 Michigan, No. 2 Ohio State has no reason to worry in Tuesday's updated College Football Playoff rankings. But given the committee's history and OSU's conference title absence, the final update may make the Buckeyes sweat.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Drive to the National Championship: Ohio State) 2016/11/27 ODV
